<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. matthaei" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matthaei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">P. matthaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is dedicated to the late Matteo Griggio, who at the age of 43 left us on 14 May 2020 due to an aneurysm. Matteo was a lively behavioural ecologist who was also very committed to nature conservation, curious about every particular aspect of nature, including 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Orthoptera</taxonomicName>
as a food source for the Rock Sparrow in Sardinia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
